{
  "texts": [
    "Figure 4a shows that the pileup drifts towards larger masses with redshift.",
    "This behaviour is highlighted in Fig. 6.",
    "We define the peak of the pileup as the maximum of the distribution for foot_5 M 1 > 25 M.",
    "With this, we can isolate three different regimes:",
    "z < 0.2: this region is dominated by the low-mass power law, and therefore the maximum leans towards 25 M, driven by the preference of the local Universe for lighter BHs."
  ]
}